  "stem": "<p>The expression 6<i>x</i>&sup2; + <i>b</i><i>x</i> + 35, where <i>b</i> is a constant, can be rewritten as (<i>h</i><i>x</i> + <i>k</i>)(<i>x</i> + <i>j</i>), where <i>h</i>, <i>k</i>, and <i>j</i> are integer constants. Which of the following must be an integer?</p>",
  "answerOptions": [
    {
      "id": "a",
      "content": "<p>35/<i>k</i></p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "b",
      "content": "<p>35/<i>h</i></p>"
    },
